Sentencas: La3+ and Pr3+ co-doped cerium oxide compositions were synthesized and examined as prospective electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) applications.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The cubic fluorite structure was confirmed with powder X-ray diffraction (XRD) and Raman studies.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: High-resolution scanning electron microscope (HR-SEM) micrographs depicted the distribution of particles in a narrowed manner on the porous structure and high-resolution transmission electron microscope (HR-TEM) image exhibited the particles are roughly in a spherical shape.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Ultraviolet and photoluminescence spectra affirmed the formation of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Thermal analysis at an intermediate temperature range affirmed the high thermal stability without any structural transitions and decompositions.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: High thermal expansion coefficient values were observed at the intermediate temperature range.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity drastically enhanced with the incorporation of La3+ dopant and Ce0.8La0.1Pr0.1O2-delta solid electrolyte expressed the highest conductivity of 1.84 x 10(-1) S/cm at 600 degrees C. Hence, Ce0.8La0.1Pr0.1O2-delta solid electrolyte is an excellent candidate in the IT-SOFC field.
Titulo: Superionic conductive La3+ and Pr3+ Co-doped cerium oxide for IT-SOFC applications
